  "body": "Currently we're displaying the Splash screen when one starts the app (before displaying login/onboarding screen). The point is that in that moment we don't have some heavy actions to do on the backend and we actually just delays the login screen waiting for the end of animation on the Splash screen (since everything is prepared much faster than the animation length).\r\n\r\nWhat we need to do:\r\n- Display Splash screen once login process is about to start (after user entered correct credentials and pressed enter)\r\n- Once Splash screen is displayed animation should be run in a loop for all the time app loading lasts\r\n- Remove Splash screen immediately when complete UI and all backend data are loaded/prepared (we don't need to wait for the animation to be done, so just stop it whenever loading on the backend is done)\r\n- Display the app, which must be fully operable from that moment",
